### ===================================================
### TESTING SCENARIOS
### ===================================================

### Scenario 1: Student looking for easy Python challenges
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?name=python&difficulty=EASY
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Scenario 2: Teacher looking for algorithm challenges
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?tags=algorithms,data-structures
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Scenario 3: Student searching for "loop" related challenges
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?name=loop
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Scenario 4: Finding medium challenges about sorting
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?name=sort&difficulty=MEDIUM&tags=sorting,arrays
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ===================================================
### EDGE CASES
### ===================================================

### Edge Case 1: Empty name parameter
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?name=
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Edge Case 2: Invalid difficulty value (should return empty or ignore)
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?difficulty=INVALID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Edge Case 3: Non-existent challenge name
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?name=ThisChallengeDoesNotExist123456789
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Edge Case 4: Special characters in name
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/search?name=c++
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ===================================================
### NOTES
### ===================================================
# - All searches return ONLY challenges with status = PUBLISHED
# - Name search is case-insensitive and uses partial matching (LIKE)
# - Multiple tags are treated as OR (at least one must match)
# - Multiple filters are combined with AND logic
# - Empty or no filters return all published challenges
